userStories.description:
Wire up the Commander.js entry point and ensure build + type-check passes.

Create `src/index.ts`:
```typescript
#!/usr/bin/env node
import { Command } from 'commander';
import { version } from '../package.json';

const program = new Command();
program
  .name('koda')
  .description('Koda — dev ticket tracker CLI')
  .version(version);

// Register all subcommands
registerLoginCommands(program);
registerConfigCommands(program);
registerProjectCommands(program);
registerTicketCommands(program);
registerCommentCommands(program);
registerAgentCommands(program);

program.parse(process.argv);
```

Verify:
- All commands registered and callable
- `bun run build` compiles to dist/
- `bun run type-check` passes
- `bun run lint` passes
- `koda --help` shows all subcommands
